fields.description:
Scoop creates a git.exe in {{%USERPROFILE%\scoop\shims}}
This binary is not the actual git, it's a shim that invokes the real one.

Source cannot handle it and returns this error:
{{git log failed with code -1}}
and then crashes.

By adding the directory fo the real git in the PATH (before the shim) the error disappers.

After using Microsoft Internet Explorer on our Bitbucket Server today to clone a new repository that took a while to open the SourceTree I repeated the action again in Chrome and found the error dialogs in the background later when checking again why the Clone/Checkout window would not appear.

One dialog "Download file..." was open with the text and a [Cancel] button:
{noformat}
Downloading from https://downloads.atlassian.com/software/sourcetree/windows/gcmw-v1.10.1.zip....
{noformat}

Apparently because I missed that and tried to checkout the same repo on a different browser the "Failed to extract file" dialog also showed with the error message:

{noformat}
System.Net.WebException: An exception occurred during a WebClient request.
System.UnauthorizedAccessException: Access to the path 'C:\Users\benz\AppData\Local\Atlassian\SourceTree\gcmw.zip' is denied.
{noformat}

